WEBVTT

00:01.764 --> 00:04.633
[Saw whirring]

00:04.667 --> 00:06.234
[Grunts]

00:06.269 --> 00:08.370
<i>Aw, come on!
It'll be fun!</i>

00:08.404 --> 00:11.506
<i>- No. It's freezing.
- Great! [Sighs]</i>

00:11.541 --> 00:15.343
Look, nobody else is out
here. It's just you and me.

00:15.378 --> 00:18.079
All right, look, I'm getting in.

00:18.114 --> 00:20.482
- Seriously.
- Go!

00:20.516 --> 00:21.817
Just give me one good
reason why you won't.

00:21.851 --> 00:25.153
- Um... it's cold.
- Okay.

00:25.188 --> 00:26.621
- It's dirty.
- Yeah.

00:26.656 --> 00:30.826
- I don't want to.
- Is that it? That's so boring.

00:30.860 --> 00:32.293
Now, that I like!

00:32.328 --> 00:35.831
That was unexpected.
I like it. That's good.

00:35.865 --> 00:38.700
Come on! Whoo!

00:38.734 --> 00:41.102
<i>Whoa, that's cold!
 Whoo!</i>

00:41.137 --> 00:44.473
Come on!
Yeah, the water's fine!

00:44.507 --> 00:49.878
Cathy! Come on!
 Take a picture!

00:49.912 --> 00:52.547
The water's fine!

00:59.155 --> 01:01.122
[Screams]

01:01.157 --> 01:03.258
<i>- Cathy?
- Oh, my god!</i>

01:03.292 --> 01:05.393
<i>[Screaming]
Cathy, it's okay.</i>

01:05.428 --> 01:08.430
- What's going on?
- Look!

01:12.568 --> 01:14.669
- You need a theme.
- I've got a theme.

01:14.704 --> 01:16.471
- What?
- Booze.

01:16.506 --> 01:20.909
People can drink at home.
You need to... amp up the fun.

01:20.943 --> 01:24.779
- Yeah, like, great music can do that.
- Yeah, get a jukebox.

01:24.814 --> 01:26.281
I got a jukebox in the back.
It's busted, though.

01:26.315 --> 01:28.550
I'm gonna get it fixed.

01:28.584 --> 01:31.286
It's got every tune ever
done by Tiffany on it.

01:31.320 --> 01:34.589
That explains why it's busted.
[Chuckles]

01:34.624 --> 01:36.691
- Maura: You need a theme.
- For a jukebox?

01:36.726 --> 01:38.268
Yeah, Maura's right. And ...

01:38.294 --> 01:39.594
And you know what?
You should switch it up.

01:39.629 --> 01:44.199
Like, one week, do '80s hair bands.
And the next week, do Southern rock.

01:44.233 --> 01:46.735
You know, I think a little
consistency would be better.

01:46.769 --> 01:49.571
Like, all Josh Groban all the time.

01:51.207 --> 01:54.442
I like it. That way, the bar
would be consistently empty.

01:54.477 --> 01:56.244
We would always have seats.
[Telephone ringing]

01:56.279 --> 01:58.380
[Chuckles] The bar will be full.
I'm working on live music.

01:58.414 --> 02:01.468
And you will always have seats.

02:01.817 --> 02:03.919
Detective Kors...
um, uh...

02:03.953 --> 02:05.887
Dirty Robber. This is Vince.

02:05.922 --> 02:10.324
Angela, what do you
think the place needs?

02:10.359 --> 02:13.528
- Yeah, Ma, you're unusually quiet.
- I'm thinking.

02:14.664 --> 02:20.602
- Paging Dr. Isles...
- No, this is a job for two, Dr. Rizzoli.

02:22.371 --> 02:23.538
[Sighs]

02:23.573 --> 02:25.840
What's up, Mom?

02:25.875 --> 02:27.876
- Nothing.
- Mm.

02:27.910 --> 02:30.612
Résumés? 
This about the job hunt?

02:30.646 --> 02:33.949
- Job hunt. How is it going?
- It's not.

02:33.983 --> 02:36.685
Nobody wants to hire a
woman of a certain age.

02:36.719 --> 02:38.720
They want to hire a 22-year-old.

02:38.754 --> 02:42.290
Well, statistically
speaking, that's not true.

02:42.325 --> 02:44.225
Although some jobs do require
more youthful employees,

02:44.260 --> 02:47.495
I think if you just expand your
universe to just ... [clears throat]

02:47.530 --> 02:49.431
Really? Statistics now?

02:49.465 --> 02:53.268
- There's comfort in numbers.
- Not for me.

02:53.302 --> 02:56.938
Résumés sent out ... 37.
Job interviews ... one.

02:56.973 --> 02:59.541
Jobs gotten ... zippo.
[Cellphones ringing]

03:01.043 --> 03:02.677
- Ah.
- Rizzoli.

03:02.712 --> 03:04.546
- Isles.
- Korsak.

03:04.580 --> 03:07.749
- Hey, I got to call you back. Yeah.
- Jane: Do it, yeah. We'll be right there.

03:07.783 --> 03:09.484
Thank you. [Beep]

03:09.518 --> 03:12.387
- I'm sorry. Ma.
- Yeah, okay, forget it.

03:12.421 --> 03:14.656
We'll talk about it later?

03:14.690 --> 03:18.827
Okay, go. Go solve crimes.
I'm staying here.

03:20.396 --> 03:21.896
Hey, Vince.

03:21.931 --> 03:25.367
Gonna stay and hang some
of your posters, okay?

03:25.401 --> 03:26.635
Oh, that's very nice of you, Angela.
Thanks.

03:26.669 --> 03:29.504
Yeah, I'm very generous.

03:29.538 --> 03:31.506
I'm also eating for free.

03:31.540 --> 03:33.508
- Ha.
- Excuse me. I'm looking for Mr. Korsak.

03:33.542 --> 03:34.876
I'm here about the job.

03:34.910 --> 03:36.444
Oh, you'll just have
to leave your résumé.

03:36.479 --> 03:40.015
We're gonna have to reschedule.
I'm sorry.

03:40.549 --> 03:44.330
- You got any experience?
- Not really. I'm just 22.

03:44.432 --> 03:47.175
You'll be fine.

